She is sitting on the train with an SSH tunnel into a cloud computing instance. 

She shuts her laptop down and begins to meditate.

On the edge of her conciousness a creature lurks. It is waiting for the right time.

She begins to hear things. Faintly at first, like the distant sound of rain undetected by others.

Then it takes the form of emotions. The frustration a man feels about the pain in his sore back. The deep loss suffered by a newly orphaned child. 
